Class OmnipotentNatsStreamingToSparkConnector<T,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.spark.streaming.receiver.Receiver<R>
      • com.logimethods.connector.nats.to_spark.NatsToSparkConnector<T,R>
        • com.logimethods.connector.nats.to_spark.OmnipotentNatsStreamingToSparkConnector<T,R>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NatsStreamingToKeyValueSparkConnectorImpl, NatsStreamingToSparkConnectorImpl

    public abstract class OmnipotentNatsStreamingToSparkConnector<T,R>
extends NatsToSparkConnector<T,R>
    A NATS to Spark Connector.

    It will transfer messages received from NATS into Spark data.

    That class extends Receiver<String>.

    An usage of this class would look like this. 

     JavaStreamingContext ssc = new JavaStreamingContext(sc, new Duration(2000));
 final JavaReceiverInputDStream<String> messages = ssc.receiverStream(NatsToSparkConnector.receiveFromNats(StorageLevel.MEMORY_ONLY(), DEFAULT_SUBJECT));
    See Also:
    Spark Streaming Custom Receivers, Serialized Form
